notes.note:
Boyer GM called again. It seems the connector for the injector they replaced has failed (Or the tech broke it). I explained this is not covered. Amy then went on to school me on how most other warranty companies handle unauthorized repairs. She explained that if there's an unauthorized repair done and it's normally covered, the warranty companies just pay it. 
I explained that that was news to me but we're not one of those warranty companies and that our warranties exclude unauthorized repairs. A.H.

Fortunately his contract covers all of these required repairs, and the parts and labour pricing is right on par, so we will be able to proceed with the claim! Parts-$719.36
Labour-$336.00 (2.8 x $120/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$124.20
Authorization-PRTVXJQT58

Matthew Puls
